# Sajtmaskin - Project Overview

AI-powered website builder where users describe a website in natural language
and get a working site generated, previewed, and deployed.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript 5.9
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui (Radix primitives)
- **AI/Generation**: Own engine (OpenAI via AI SDK) default; v0 Platform API fallback when V0_FALLBACK_BUILDER=y
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (Supabase) via Drizzle ORM
- **Cache**: Redis (Upstash/ioredis)
- **State**: Zustand (auth), React hooks (builder state)
- **Payments**: Stripe
- **Deploy target**: Vercel (user sites deployed via Vercel API)
- **Storage**: Vercel Blob (AI-generated images)

## Architecture

```
User prompt -> Builder UI -> Own engine (default) or v0 Platform API (fallback) -> Generated code -> Preview -> Deploy to Vercel
```

- **Own engine**: `src/lib/gen/` — streamText, runtime scaffolds, autofix, preview. Kräver OPENAI_API_KEY.
- **v0 fallback**: När V0_FALLBACK_BUILDER=y skickas till v0 Platform API. Kräver V0_API_KEY.
- **Template gallery**: `src/lib/templates/` — user-facing browsing/search/discovery surface, not the runtime scaffold registry.
- **Research lane**: `v0_vercel_agents/official_docs/`, `research/external-templates/`, and `src/lib/gen/template-library/` — curated docs/reference material used to improve scaffolds, not to replace them at runtime.

